attacks.name: Yawn
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

data.flavorText: Alolan home cooking involves drying Slowpoke tails and then simmering them into a salty stew.

data.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Big Yawn
attacks.text: Both this Pokémon and the Defending Pokémon are now Asleep.

attacks.name: Shot in the Dark
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If either of them is tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

data.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Tail Lure
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

data.flavorText: It lazes vacantly near water. If something bites its tail, it won't even notice for a whole day.

data.name: Slowpoke & Psyduck-GX
rules: TAG TEAM rule: When your TAG TEAM is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 3 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Ditch and Splash
attacks.text: Discard any number of Supporter cards from your hand. This attack does 40 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Thrilling Times-GX
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 100 more damage. If this Pokémon has at least 6 extra Water Energy attached to it (in addition to this attack's cost), flip 10 coins instead, and this attack does 100 more damage for each heads. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Amnesia
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Tail Strike
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

data.name: Slowpoke

attacks.name: Spacing Out
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Scavenge
attacks.text: Discard a Psychic Energy attached to this Pokémon. If you do, put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

data.flavorText: It is always vacantly lost in thought, but no one knows what it is thinking about. It is good at fishing with its tail.

attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: Its long tail often breaks off. It doesn't really feel any pain, though, and the tail grows back, so Slowpoke isn't particularly bothered.

attacks.name: Growl
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

data.flavorText: There are some places where Slowpoke is worshiped because of a long-standing belief that whenever Slowpoke yawns, it rains.
